                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="153945" author="yong.fan" created="Sun, 29 May 2016 14:35:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Because the patch 14497 made the test_15c obsolete, there was no special fix for that. So depends on whether we want to port 14497 patch to b2_7_fe, if no, then we need other solution for test_15c failure.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="153724" author="jhammond" created="Thu, 26 May 2016 18:35:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;15c is failing on b2_7_fe review testing. See &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/35235730-2199-11e6-9089-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/35235730-2199-11e6-9089-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;. Is there a fix for this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="153365" author="yong.fan" created="Tue, 24 May 2016 16:03:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch 14497 resolve the issue that was tested by test_15c. It seems that such patch has NOT been ported to b2_7_fe yet. So test_15c should be still valid on b2_7_fe unless you are making some interoperability tests with master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="153346" author="jhammond" created="Tue, 24 May 2016 15:12:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fan Yong, we are seeing this on &lt;tt&gt;b2_7_fe&lt;/tt&gt; should the test be disabled there?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="118685" author="yong.fan" created="Tue, 16 Jun 2015 15:10:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;sanity-lfsck test_15c will be obsolete because of the patch:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/14497/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/14497/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
